{"word":"H5734 - עַדְנָה - ʻAdnâh - ad-naw' - Adnah","slug":"H5734","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עַדְנָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻAdnâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ad-naw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Adnah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>עדנה</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>‛adnâh</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>ad-naw'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Adnah = \"pleasure\" <ol><li>a Manassite who deserted from Saul and joined David at Ziklag</li><li>a captain in charge of over 300,000 men of Judah in the time of Jehoshaphat</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H5727\">H5727</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4574\">H4574</a>, <a href=\"#/H5719\">H5719</a>, <a href=\"#/H5720\">H5720</a>, <a href=\"#/H5721\">H5721</a>, <a href=\"#/H5722\">H5722</a>, <a href=\"#/H5727\">H5727</a>, <a href=\"#/H5730\">H5730</a>, <a href=\"#/H5731\">H5731</a>, <a href=\"#/H5733\">H5733</a>, <a href=\"#/H6112\">H6112</a>"}]}